UObjectToolTips.VehicleModStaticMeshAttachmentData:Colli:
If set to true, this will weld the mesh locally on all clients.
This cause the static mesh to affect vehicle handling.

Prefer leaving this value false, unless absolutely necessary. A cosmetic only mesh does not need this enabled.

If enabling this feature, do not leave this property without hooking it up to a row in the game data.
We need to be able to hotfix this off in an emergency.
Self-collisions can easily become a problem with complexity a round welding and replication.

NOTE: If true, the Static mesh component will not be replicated, and cannot be referred to via replicated variables or RPCs.
Physics welding is not replicated as part of scene component attachment.
The local spawning of the mesh is to avoid issues with intra-collisions from a static mesh that has collision set on server, but not welded on client.

NOTE: Welding does not function well with sockets.
This feature will place it at the socket/bone you specify.
But it will actually be welded to the root, not the socket.
This means any sockets on animated bones, will NOT move the mesh.
Use a non-welded mesh if it needs animation.
UObjectToolTips.VehicleModStaticMeshAttachmentData:Attac:
The name of the socket at which to place the static mesh.
The relative transform will move the static mesh relative to this socket.
If no socket name is provided, the static mesh will be relative to the center of the vehicle skeletal mesh.
UObjectToolTips.TargetingSourceContext:SourceActor: The optional actor the targeting request sources from (i.e. player/projectile/etc)
UObjectToolTips.TargetingSourceContext:InstigatorActor: The optional instigator the targeting request is owned by (i.e. owner of a projectile)
UObjectToolTips.TargetingSourceContext:SourceLocation: The optional location the targeting request will source from (i.e. do AOE targeting at x/y/z location)
UObjectToolTips.TargetingSourceContext:SourceObject: The optional reference to a source uobject to use in the context
UObjectToolTips.TargetingSourceContext:SourceSocketName: The optional socket name to use on the source actor (if an actor is defined)
UObjectToolTips.VehicleModStaticMeshAttachmentData:Relat:
The relative transform to spawn the static mesh at.
If AttachSocketName is provided, this will be relative to the socket location.
Otherwise, it is relative to center of skeletal mesh.
UObjectToolTips.VehicleModStaticMeshAttachmentData:Stati: The static mesh to spawn on the vehicle.
